<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="modular">
  <title>Modular Arithmetic</title>
  <introduction>
    <blockquote>
      What goes up, must come down
      Spinnin' wheel, got ta go round
      Talkin' 'bout your troubles it's a cryin' sin
      Ride a painted pony, Let the spinnin' wheel spin
      <em>(Source:
      <q>Spinnin' Wheel</q>, Blood, Sweat, and Tears)</em>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Cycles are everywhere.
      So are integers.
      Modular arithmetic combines the two by wrapping the integers around a circle.
    </p>
    <p>
      Thanks to Tom Judson for material used in this chapter.
      David Weathers also contributed a section.
    </p>
  </introduction>
